{"title": "George M\u00fcller of Bristol", "description": "George Muller was a great hero of faith. His greatest aim was to demonstrate that God answers prayer and can be trusted for every minute detail of life. Spending countless hours asking God to provide his needs, he only relied upon God. God called him to care for orphans and he conducted his orphanage in the same way, on faith alone. When a certain need was apparent, they would immediately go to God in prayer. In this dynamic dependance on God, He always proved faithful. He also established over a hundred schools, educating over a hundred thousand people! His example of absolute dependence on God stands in the gap of history to declare that God is enough, and He is faithful! (Summary by Kimberly Krause)<br /><br />Dedicated proof-listeners: Larry Wilson, Fiddlesticks, & Kimberly Krause", "duration": 44940, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "10006", "name": "Arthur T. Pierson"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/georgemuller_1407_librivox/george_muller_1408.jpg", "copyright_year": "1899", "genres": ["Biography & Autobiography"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Dave Harrell"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Dave Harrell"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction & A Prefatory Word", "readers": [8393], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/georgemuller_1407_librivox/georgemullerofbristol_00_pierson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 533}, {"section": 1, "title": "From His Birth to His New Birth", "readers": [8393], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/georgemuller_1407_librivox/georgemullerofbristol_01_pierson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1604}, {"section": 2, "title": "The New Birth and the New Life", "readers": [8393], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/georgemuller_1407_librivox/georgemullerofbristol_02_pierson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1671}, {"section": 3, "title": "Making Ready the Chosen Vessel", "readers": [8393], "p